fields.name: Marcus "Big Grape" Johnson
fields.criminal_record: Multiple arrests for gang-related activities. Known OG of Grape Street.

fields.name: Tyrone "T-Bone" Williams
fields.criminal_record: Multiple arrests for gang-related activities. Known Shot Caller of Grape Street.

fields.name: DeAndre "Lil Loc" Davis
fields.criminal_record: Multiple arrests for gang-related activities. Known Soldier of Grape Street.

fields.name: Jamal "Grape" Thompson
fields.criminal_record: Multiple arrests for gang-related activities. Known Enforcer of Grape Street.

fields.name: Kevin "K-Dog" Brown
fields.criminal_record: Multiple arrests for gang-related activities. Known Soldier of Grape Street.

fields.name: Derek Fierro
fields.rank: Varrio Grape Shotcaller / Tiny Wynos Head
fields.criminal_record: High-ranking Varrio Grape 13 member. Controls Tiny Wynos subset. Multiple arrests for weapons possession, drug trafficking, and assault. Known for violent enforcement. Primary contact with Mexican Mafia. Considered armed and extremely dangerous.
fields.notes: Primary leader of Varrio Grape operations. Strategic decision maker. Has strong ties to Mexican Mafia through family connections. Expert in weapons trafficking.

fields.name: Tracy Nanjares
fields.criminal_record: Leader of Gangster Locos subset within RVG13. Known for drug distribution operations. Multiple arrests for narcotics sales, robbery, and extortion. Controls street-level operations in South Central.
fields.notes: Oversees day-to-day drug operations for Varrio Grape. Known for aggressive business tactics. Has connections with The Amendola Crew for supply chain.

fields.name: Tyler Atienza
fields.criminal_record: Second-in-command of Gangster Locos. Assists Tracy Nanjares in operations. Arrests for assault, weapons charges, and gang activity. Known for recruitment of younger members.
fields.notes: Right hand to Big Greedy. Handles enforcement and collections. Suspected in multiple violent incidents against rival gangs.

fields.name: Sincere Helms
fields.criminal_record: Top-ranking Baby Locs member. Leads Young Militant Shottas (YMS) subset. Multiple warrants for murder, attempted murder, weapons trafficking, and organized crime. Extremely violent. Consider armed and dangerous at all times.
fields.notes: Most wanted GSC member. Primary target in Operation Grape Harvest. Suspected in 7+ homicides. Strong connections to Hoover Criminals. Known to order retaliatory strikes.

fields.name: Daron Holland
fields.criminal_record: Second-in-command of YMS. Known enforcer for Baby Locs operations. Multiple arrests for assault with deadly weapon, robbery, and gang conspiracy. Close associate of Sincere Helms.
fields.notes: Primary enforcer for Snatch#5. Carries out violent orders. Suspected in multiple drive-by shootings against PJRC and BHB.

fields.name: Reilly Morkins
fields.criminal_record: Leader of OthaSideBabies subset. Operates second major faction within Baby Locs. Arrests for drug trafficking, weapons possession, and attempted murder. Known for extreme violence.
fields.notes: Runs OBS operations semi-independently. Competes with YMS but loyal to overall GSC structure. Has Armenian connections for drug supply.

fields.name: Christopher Olivas
fields.criminal_record: Second-in-command of OBS. Younger member rising through ranks. Arrests for narcotics sales, assault, and gang participation. Known for social media threats against rivals.
fields.notes: Tech-savvy member handling social media warfare. Uses online platforms to coordinate and taunt rivals. Under surveillance for online threats.

fields.title: Operation Grape Harvest - GSC Investigation
fields.description: Comprehensive investigation into Grape Street Crip operations, focusing on narcotics distribution network and violent conflicts with rival gangs, particularly BHRB and F13.

fields.title: Blood vs Crip Territory War - South Central
fields.description: Escalating violence between Blood and Crip factions in South Central. Multiple shootings and retaliations documented. Focus on BHRB and GSC conflict.

fields.title: Multi-Gang Narcotics Distribution Network
fields.description: Investigation into coordinated drug trafficking operation involving GSC, HCG, and PBGC. Interstate distribution suspected.

fields.title: Gang-Related Homicides - Rancho District
fields.description: String of murders linked to ongoing feud between GSC and PJRC over Rancho territory. 5 victims in past 3 months.

fields.title: Illegal Weapons Trafficking Ring
fields.description: Intelligence suggests large-scale weapons importation and distribution. GSC and allied gangs suspected of coordinating purchases.

fields.title: Organized Crime - Extortion and Racketeering
fields.description: Local businesses reporting systematic extortion by gang members. Pattern suggests organized operation across multiple territories.

fields.title: Gang Summit Intelligence - Potential Conflict
fields.description: Intercepted communications suggest planned confrontation between allied and rival factions. High risk of major violence.

fields.title: Cold Case Review - 2024 Jordan Downs Shooting
fields.description: Re-opening investigation into mass shooting at Jordan Downs. New evidence suggests GSC involvement and BHRB retaliation.

fields.title: Juvenile Gang Recruitment Investigation
fields.description: Increased gang recruitment activity targeting minors. Multiple gangs competing for young members in South Central schools.

fields.title: Cross-Gang Alliance Monitoring
fields.description: Unusual alliance patterns observed. Blood-Crip cooperation between GSC and BPS requires surveillance and analysis.

fields.title: Drive-By Shooting Series - Florence Corridor
fields.description: Series of coordinated drive-by shootings along Florence Avenue. F13 and GSC engaging in active warfare.

fields.title: Money Laundering Operation - Front Businesses
fields.description: Several businesses suspected of being gang fronts for money laundering. Financial crimes unit investigating GSC connections.

fields.title: Operation Grape Harvest - Comprehensive GSC Investigation
fields.description: Primary investigation into both Rancho Varrio Grape 13 and Grape Street Rancho Crip operations. Focus on leadership structure, narcotics distribution, weapons trafficking, and violent crimes. Target: Dismantling entire Grape Street organization.

fields.title: Blood Alliance vs Grape Street War
fields.description: Investigation into coordinated Blood gang warfare against Grape Street. BHB and HVB alliance targeting both RVG13 and GSC. Multiple homicides, drive-by shootings, and retaliations. High casualty count.

fields.title: Crip-on-Crip Violence - Rancho Territory War
fields.description: PJRC vs GSC territorial conflict over Rancho district. Escalating violence with multiple shootings. Investigation into root causes and potential mediation possibilities.

fields.title: Amendola-Grape Distribution Network
fields.description: Multi-agency investigation into sophisticated drug distribution network. The Amendola Crew coordinating with both Grape factions. Interstate trafficking suspected. DEA cooperation.

fields.title: dasd
fields.description: sadsad

fields.title: Armenian-GSC Weapons Trafficking Ring
fields.description: Investigation into weapons supply chain from Armenian Criminal Enterprise to Baby Locs. Large-scale firearms trafficking. ATF joint operation.

fields.title: Mexican Mafia - RVG13 Connection Investigation
fields.description: Investigating nature of Mexican Mafia relationship with Rancho Varrio Grape 13. Tax payments, protection, or deeper involvement unclear. Prison-street gang coordination suspected.

fields.title: Chinatown Money Laundering Operation
fields.description: Financial crimes investigation. Chinatown organization suspected of laundering drug proceeds for Baby Locs. Complex shell company structure.

fields.title: The Black Car - Unknown Entity Investigation
fields.description: Mysterious "Black Car" organization mentioned in intercepted communications. Relationship to Baby Locs unknown. Surveillance ongoing.

fields.title: Hoover Criminals - GSC Alliance Operations
fields.description: Investigating strong alliance between HCG and Baby Locs. Multiple joint operations documented. Coordinated territorial expansion.

fields.title: Juvenile Recruitment - Tiny Wynos & YMS
fields.description: Investigation into aggressive recruitment of minors by Tiny Wynos (RVG13) and Young Militant Shottas (GSC). School-based operations.

fields.title: Social Media Gang Activity & Threats
fields.description: Monitoring online gang activity. Sosa#4k and other members using social platforms for threats, coordination, and recruitment. Cyber crimes unit involved.

fields.title: Sureño Network - Terror Town 13 Partnership
fields.description: Investigating coordination between RVG13 and TT13. Shared distribution territories and protection arrangements.

fields.title: Derek "Ruger" Fierro - Leadership Investigation
fields.description: Focused investigation on primary RVG13 leader. Weapons trafficking connections, Mexican Mafia ties, and violent enforcement activities.

fields.title: Cold Case Review - 2023-2025 Grape Street Murders
fields.description: Re-opening multiple unsolved homicides. New evidence and witness testimony. Cases linked to ongoing gang warfare.

fields.title: Drive-by shooting on Grape Street
fields.description: Suspected BHRB members conducted drive-by targeting Grape Street territory. Multiple shots fired, 2 civilians injured.

fields.title: Narcotics seizure at Rancho
fields.description: Large drug operation interrupted. GSC and PJRC members present, territorial dispute over distribution.

fields.title: Gang-related homicide - Florence area
fields.description: Suspected GSC member killed in F13 territory. Retaliation expected.

fields.title: Weapons trafficking operation
fields.description: Intelligence suggests GSC and HCG coordinating weapons acquisition. Investigation ongoing.

fields.title: Jordan Downs Drive-By - Multiple Casualties
fields.description: BHB members conducted drive-by shooting targeting Baby Locs territory. 4 shot, 1 fatally. Suspected retaliation for previous GSC action. Snatch#5 believed to be target.

fields.title: Rancho Territory Shooting - Gang Member Killed
fields.location: Rancho District, near PJ territory border
fields.description: RVG13 member shot and killed in disputed territory. Suspect vehicle matches PJRC descriptions. Retaliation expected.

fields.title: Major Narcotics Seizure - Multi-Gang Operation
fields.description: 50 kilos cocaine seized. Evidence suggests coordinated distribution network between RVG13, Amendola Crew, and TT13. Multiple arrests made.

fields.title: Weapons Cache Discovered - Armenian Connection
fields.description: 30+ firearms recovered. Links to ACE weapons trafficking. Baby Locs members arrested at scene. Investigation ongoing.

fields.title: East Coast Crips Ambush - GSC Confrontation
fields.description: ECC members ambushed GSC vehicle. Gunfire exchanged, 3 wounded. Ongoing Crip-on-Crip warfare escalating.

fields.title: Florencia 13 Conflict - Sureño Dispute
fields.description: Major confrontation over drug distribution territory. Multiple injuries. Mexican Mafia involvement suspected in attempting to mediate.

fields.title: Social Media Threats Lead to Shooting
fields.description: Online threats between Sosa#4k and HVB members escalated to real-world violence. 2 injured in shooting. Digital evidence collected.
